The Speaker of the Benue State House of Assembly, Titus Uba has emerged the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, governorship candidate in Benue State. Uba won the ticket to represent the party in the 2023 polls in a keenly-contested election held at the Aper Aku Stadium in Makurdi on Thursday. The Speaker won 21 out of the 23 LGAs in the state. His closest challenger, Benson Abounu won in Otukpo and Ogbadibo LGAs. Benue PDP governorship primaries results below. ADO
